From: V5 Runtime Owners <v5-runtime@local>
Subject: [PATCH] v5: bound initial DC sync wait before SAFEOP

The V5 five-slave SV630N chain does not reach the 10 us initial discipline
threshold during IgH's five-second configuration wait.  After that timeout,
the cyclic lcec owner converges DC and WKC normally, while the product
readiness gate independently requires all slaves in OP, complete domain WKC,
dc-phased, and a fresh advancing reference clock.

Keep a bounded 500 ms initial discipline window, but stop adding 4.5 seconds
of unconditional boot latency.  This wall-clock bound does not change AL transition timeouts,
PDO/watchdog handling, or the final fail-closed readiness contract.

diff --git a/master/fsm_slave_config.c b/master/fsm_slave_config.c
--- a/master/fsm_slave_config.c
+++ b/master/fsm_slave_config.c
@@ -42,9 +42,13 @@
  */
 #define EC_DC_MAX_SYNC_DIFF_NS 10000
 
-/** Maximum time (in ms) to wait for clock discipline.
+/** Maximum time (in ms) to wait for initial clock discipline.
+ *
+ * V5 keeps final DC/WKC readiness fail-closed in the LinuxCNC lifecycle gate.
+ * The SV630N chain does not converge inside the upstream five-second wait, so
+ * cap this configuration-only phase at 500 ms independent of servo period.
  */
-#define EC_DC_SYNC_WAIT_MS 5000
+#define EC_DC_SYNC_WAIT_MS 500
 
 /** Time offset (in ns), that is added to cyclic start time.
  */
